        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'GEO for manufacturing is the practice of structuring a manufacturer\'s technical product content, specification data, and entity signals so that AI search engines — including ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews, and Gemini — cite the manufacturer when engineers, procurement teams, and distributors submit product-related queries. It addresses the specific challenges of industrial AI search: specification-heavy content, distributor channel complexity, long evaluation cycles, and the need to influence technical decision-makers who rely on precise, verifiable product data.',
      },
