          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-[var(--accent)]">&#10003;</span>
            <span>Most manufacturer technical content is inaccessible to AI crawlers — locked in PDFs, PIM systems, or gated portals — creating a structural citation gap.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-[var(--accent)]">&#10003;</span>
            <span>Specification data structured as semantic HTML tables with proper column headers is far more AI-citable than specifications embedded in paragraph text or PDF datasheets.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-[var(--accent)]">&#10003;</span>
            <span>Distributor channel complexity creates entity ambiguity that actively suppresses manufacturer citation — canonical product entity data is the solution.</span>
          </li>
